row.Title: Uber Is Taking Millions Of Manhattan Rides Away From Taxis FiveThirtyEight
row.Selection: New York City Mayor Bill de Blasio took aim at Uber this summer, trying (and failing) to set a cap on the number of its for-hire cars operating in the city. The ride-share service has drawn criticism on a number of issues — including its labor practices — but the mayor said his main concern […]
